    <header>
        <h1><marquee height="45">Jajangmyeon</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>200g Korean black bean paste (Chunjang)</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1 cup diced pork or beef</li>
            <li>1 cup diced onion</li>
            <li>1 cup diced zucchini</li>
            <li>1 cup diced potatoes</li>
            <li>1 cup diced carrots</li>
            <li>2 cups chicken or vegetable broth</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons soy sauce</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon sugar</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon black pepper</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons cornstarch mixed with 3 tablespoons water (slurry)</li>
            <li>4 servings of Korean wheat noodles (or substitute with Chinese noodles)</li>
            <li>Sliced cucumber for garnish (optional)</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Jajangmyeon</li>
            <li>Korean</li>
            <li>Noodles</li>
            <li>Black Bean Sauce</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Cook the Korean wheat noodles according to the package instructions. Drain and set aside.</li>
            <li>In a large pan or wok, heat vegetable oil over medium-high heat. Add the diced pork or beef and cook until browned.</li>
            <li>Add the diced onion, zucchini, potatoes, and carrots to the pan. Stir-fry until the vegetables are slightly softened.</li>
            <li>Move the vegetables and meat to one side of the pan and add the Korean black bean paste (Chunjang) to the empty side. Cook the paste for a few minutes to release its flavors.</li>
            <li>Combine the black bean paste with the vegetables and meat. Add chicken or vegetable broth, soy sauce, sugar, and black pepper. Simmer for about 15-20 minutes, or until the vegetables are fully cooked.</li>
            <li>Stir in the cornstarch slurry to thicken the sauce. Continue cooking until the sauce reaches your desired consistency.</li>
            <li>Serve the jajangmyeon sauce over the cooked noodles. Garnish with sliced cucumbers if desired.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious Jajangmyeon!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

